The paper focuses on fraud detection using a combination of deep neural networks and spectral graph analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fraud detection on a signed graph. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a novel framework that combines deep neural networks and spectral graph analysis. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper deals with fraud detection. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper uses spectral graph analysis to capture the most useful topology information of the network. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a novel framework that combines deep neural networks and spectral graph analysis for fraud detection.
